delegating employee health
care out of the Analysis Lab

98
00:08:46,166 --> 00:08:48,125
just 'cuz I've got
a physician's license?

99
00:08:48,208 --> 00:08:50,750
I mean, yeah, sure,
I'm also a latent criminal.

100
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:52,833
But it's not like that gives
them the right to treat me

101
00:08:52,916 --> 00:08:55,500
like a freakin' slave
while I'm down here.

102
00:08:55,583 --> 00:08:57,333
Uh. Right.

103
00:08:57,416 --> 00:09:00,625
Let's see. Akane.
It's Akane, right?

104
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:05,875
You must be on the fast track
if you're already an Inspector.

105
00:09:05,958 --> 00:09:07,416
Do me a favor and
reform the system

106
00:09:07,500 --> 00:09:09,541
once you become a
high-ranking official.

107
00:09:09,625 --> 00:09:12,375
You could start by having
them put in a swimming pool

108
00:09:12,458 --> 00:09:16,208
and a bar area in
the CID. Pretty please.

109
00:09:16,291 --> 00:09:20,583
I don't know. Um. How's
Kogami's treatment been?

110
00:09:20,666 --> 00:09:22,875
Oh. Hold on.

111
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:28,250
I don't know where
you were aiming,

112
00:09:28,333 --> 00:09:31,375
but you managed to land a direct
hit right on his spinal cord.

113
00:09:31,458 --> 00:09:33,958
So he's still got a
little more healing to do.

114
00:09:34,041 --> 00:09:36,041
Not exactly up to
walking and talking yet.

115
00:09:36,125 --> 00:09:39,541
He's not up for having
any fun in bed either.

116
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:47,458
I suppose it'd be okay
to peek in on him though.

117
00:09:47,541 --> 00:09:50,125
He won't know you're there,
of course. It's up to you.

118
00:09:50,208 --> 00:09:53,750
No that's alright. I don't
wanna risk waking him.

119
00:09:53,833 --> 00:09:55,708
He should be back
to normal tomorrow.

120
00:09:55,791 --> 00:09:57,541
He just needs a
full day of rest.

121
00:09:57,625 --> 00:10:01,208
Check back in the morning
and you can talk to him.

122
00:10:02,041 --> 00:10:03,458
Okay.

123
00:10:39,166 --> 00:10:40,708
Umm.

124
00:10:41,333 --> 00:10:44,500
Sorry, but... is there
another tablet I can use?

125
00:10:44,583 --> 00:10:45,833
Well, the last I checked,

126
00:10:45,916 --> 00:10:48,583
Enforcer Kogami was using
all the spare equipment.

127
00:10:48,666 --> 00:10:53,000
Uh, but how could he,
I mean, Kogami's still.

128
00:10:53,083 --> 00:10:57,041
Recovering from
being shot? Yes, he is.

129
00:10:58,125 --> 00:10:59,875
Jeez, that hurt.

130
00:11:00,333 --> 00:11:01,583
Here.

131
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:04,833
You can use mine.

132
00:11:04,916 --> 00:11:06,666
Oh, thanks a lot.

133
00:11:06,750 --> 00:11:09,750
Yeah, I know I'm late.
Sorry. Well hello.

134
00:11:09,833 --> 00:11:11,916
I wasn't aware that you
were on duty tonight.

135
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:13,500
Uhh. Yeah.

136
00:11:13,583 --> 00:11:16,166
Must be tough on ya comin'
in after last night.

137
00:11:16,250 --> 00:11:18,208
Well, let's just keep our
fingers crossed today's

138
00:11:18,291 --> 00:11:20,666
a little more laid back.

139
00:11:21,166 --> 00:11:23,333
Elevated Area
Stress Level warning.

140
00:11:23,416 --> 00:11:25,333
A Psycho-Pass above
the regulation value has

141
00:11:25,416 --> 00:11:28,583
been detected inside Iko Gryce
Hill in the Adachi Ward.

142
00:11:28,666 --> 00:11:31,916
The on duty Inspector
and available Enforcers

143
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:34,833
are immediately required
for intervention at the scene.

144
00:11:34,916 --> 00:11:37,333
That's what I get for
askin' for a peaceful day.

145
00:11:38,666 --> 00:11:42,416
Aw, man. Too bad our shift
just ended. Have fun!

146
00:11:42,500 --> 00:11:45,083
Do you want some backup?
I'll cover for Kogami.

147
00:11:45,166 --> 00:11:47,833
Thanks, but I'm sure
we'll be okay on our own.

148
00:11:47,916 --> 00:11:51,458
Well, Inspector Akane.
You ready to head out?

149
00:12:05,916 --> 00:12:08,166
We've had drones posted on each

150
00:12:08,250 --> 00:12:10,041
of the mall's exits since
the warning was triggered.

151
00:12:10,125 --> 00:12:12,750
But they haven't managed
to catch anyone yet.

152
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:14,166
More specifically,

153
00:12:14,250 --> 00:12:16,875
they haven't caught whoever's
raising the area stress.

154
00:12:16,958 --> 00:12:18,916
So they're still
somewhere in the mall.

155
00:12:19,000 --> 00:12:21,291
Will we need to use
the Dominators for this?

156
00:12:21,375 --> 00:12:24,166
We should keep them on us,
just as a precaution.

157
00:12:24,250 --> 00:12:27,166
But I sincerely doubt that
we'll need to un-holster them.

158
00:12:27,250 --> 00:12:30,000
Enough chit-chat. Shall we go?

159
00:12:44,083 --> 00:12:45,333
Are you too uncomfortable?

160
00:12:45,416 --> 00:12:46,750
I thought you'd
be okay with this.

161
00:12:46,833 --> 00:12:49,083
Don't all you kids love
playing with holo-suits?

162
00:12:49,166 --> 00:12:52,500
Yeah, I'm just not used to
my whole body being an avatar.

163
00:12:52,583 --> 00:12:53,416
I'm not giving up.

164
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,041
Stop it cut it out.

165
00:12:56,791 --> 00:12:58,791
I'm not doubting
your persistence!

166
00:12:58,875 --> 00:13:00,166
Better not.

167
00:13:02,291 --> 00:13:04,166
Come on. Quit
playing hard to get.

168
00:13:05,041 --> 00:13:06,375
Oh. There he is.

169
00:13:06,458 --> 00:13:09,000
The guy hiding behind
the column back there.

170
00:13:10,083 --> 00:13:11,166
Are you sure?

171
00:13:11,250 --> 00:13:13,083
How can you tell
without using a scanner?

172
00:13:13,166 --> 00:13:15,916
It's hard to explain, but a
beast can sniff out his own.

173
00:13:20,916 --> 00:13:21,958
Excuse me, sir.

174
00:13:22,041 --> 00:13:23,375
Would you mind

175
00:13:23,458 --> 00:13:25,583
if we took a quick measure
of your Psycho-Pass?

176
00:13:46,125 --> 00:13:48,000
Oh, buddy. Now that is cloudy.

177
00:13:48,083 --> 00:13:51,250
Without a doubt, you are in
need of some emergency therapy.

178
00:13:51,333 --> 00:13:53,916
I need you to
please come with me.

179
00:13:54,000 --> 00:13:57,333
What? But why?
I haven't done anything wrong.

180
00:14:01,125 --> 00:14:03,583
I'm amazed you can spot
latent criminals like that.

181
00:14:03,666 --> 00:14:05,458
You can tell when
they're up to no good, but...

182
00:14:05,541 --> 00:14:08,833
The best way to catch a
bad guy is to think like one.

183
00:14:08,916 --> 00:14:11,250
Doesn't matter if you're
a good guy, though.

184
00:14:11,333 --> 00:14:12,708
Being able to think
like a criminal

185
00:14:12,791 --> 00:14:15,458
is about the same as
being one to the system.

186
00:14:15,541 --> 00:14:17,791
It all registers the
same and that's

187
00:14:17,875 --> 00:14:21,541
why I've got such a crazy
high Crime Coefficient.

188
00:14:22,250 --> 00:14:24,000
Thanks to my skills
as a peace officer,

189
00:14:24,083 --> 00:14:27,041
I'm now treated as a
glorified hunting dog.

190
00:14:27,125 --> 00:14:28,791
You were great.

191
00:14:28,875 --> 00:14:31,000
But I was just
useless out there.

192
00:14:31,083 --> 00:14:34,083
That's not true,
you were quite helpful.

193
00:14:34,166 --> 00:14:36,583
Enforcers can't even
show themselves in public

194
00:14:36,666 --> 00:14:38,625
without an Inspector
by their side.

195
00:14:38,708 --> 00:14:39,833
But that's nothing.

196
00:14:39,916 --> 00:14:42,791
Don't get me wrong here.

197
00:14:46,041 --> 00:14:47,875
Look, after you bring the
Enforcers to the scene,

198
00:14:47,958 --> 00:14:51,375
they're really only thing you
need to worry about.

199
00:14:51,458 --> 00:14:53,708
Don't let em slack off,
run away or cause trouble.

200
00:14:53,791 --> 00:14:57,250
And that's it easy peasy
that's all there is to your job.

201
00:14:57,333 --> 00:14:58,625
So you're saying
that it's my job

202
00:14:58,708 --> 00:15:00,875
to stand back
and do nothing?

203
00:15:12,000 --> 00:15:15,083
How 'bout some company,
Inspector? If you don't mind.

204
00:15:15,166 --> 00:15:17,000
Sure.

205
00:15:25,166 --> 00:15:27,666
I thought you were already
off duty for the night.

206
00:15:28,125 --> 00:15:31,166
You do realize that we
Enforcers are prisoners, right?

207
00:15:31,833 --> 00:15:33,250
Creamer.

208
00:15:33,333 --> 00:15:34,583
Even when we're not on the
clock, our access is restricted

209
00:15:34,666 --> 00:15:37,125
to the CID floor and
our own personal quarters.

210
00:15:37,208 --> 00:15:39,250
I'm sorry I acted
like a jerk earlier.

211
00:15:39,333 --> 00:15:42,458
I was just jokin' around but
I got a little carried away.

212
00:15:42,541 --> 00:15:44,000
In case you haven't
noticed, most of the women

213
00:15:44,083 --> 00:15:46,458
who work here can
be scary as all hell.

214
00:15:46,541 --> 00:15:49,500
So I'm actually happy we've got
such a cute girl around now.

215
00:15:49,583 --> 00:15:51,875
Really, I'm glad
you're here, Akane.

216
00:15:51,958 --> 00:15:53,916
Oh, yeah. You mind
if I call you Akane?

217
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,916
I don't see why not.

218
00:15:56,000 --> 00:16:00,333
You've got me curious.
Inspector for the MWPSB.

219
00:16:00,416 --> 00:16:02,791
I mean, talk about a crazy
ass place to wanna work.

220
00:16:02,875 --> 00:16:04,125
Why'd you pick this job?

221
00:16:06,708 --> 00:16:09,000
Don't think I'm right
for it. Do you?

222
00:16:09,083 --> 00:16:12,625
You're asking that after
what happened yesterday?

223
00:16:12,708 --> 00:16:14,958
I doubt many people
would say you are.

224
00:16:15,041 --> 00:16:17,125
Sibyl's Judgment of
my job aptitude had me

225
00:16:17,208 --> 00:16:20,208
well over the PSB's
employment standards.

226
00:16:21,083 --> 00:16:23,541
Yeah, exactly,
that's what I don't get.

227
00:16:23,625 --> 00:16:25,875
The standards for
the PSB are top tier.

228
00:16:25,958 --> 00:16:27,500
So your rankings
must've qualified you

229
00:16:27,583 --> 00:16:29,250
for other careers too.

230
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:32,208
I mean, couldn't you have
just picked a different job?

231
00:16:32,291 --> 00:16:33,583
Yeah.

232
00:16:33,666 --> 00:16:35,041
Actually.

233
00:16:35,125 --> 00:16:38,291
I got an A ranking for
all thirteen ministries

234
00:16:38,375 --> 00:16:39,666
and six companies.

235
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:42,166
What? Seriously?

236
00:16:42,250 --> 00:16:43,833
Yeah, but.

237
00:16:43,916 --> 00:16:45,041
With all the other jobs,

238
00:16:45,125 --> 00:16:47,125
I wasn't the only one
to get an A ranking.

239
00:16:47,208 --> 00:16:49,791
There was at least one other
person that got the same grade.

240
00:16:49,875 --> 00:16:51,583
But I was the only one

241
00:16:51,666 --> 00:16:55,083
who scored an A ranking
for the MWPSB.

242
00:16:55,166 --> 00:16:58,250
There were more than
500 students graded.

243
00:16:58,333 --> 00:17:01,791
So I thought there must be some
job I was meant to do here,

